Sentencas: A model of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anodes, based on spherical particle packing, was numerically studied by means of the three-dimensional particle element method (PEM), which is a discrete element method.
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: In this model, the porous SOFC consisted of three-component particles: electronic, ionic and void particles (pores).
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: A triple-phase boundary (TPB) was defined by the local site where the three-component phases came into contact.
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: The length of TPB (TPB density) was calculated by the contact circle length between the ionic and electronic particles at the TPB site.
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: In the present study, the effect of porosity could be treated in addition to the grain size of the solid phase.
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes

Sentencas: Because the effect of porosity was treated in detail, our numerical results were in good agreement with the experimentally measured TPB density.
Titulo: A modeling study of porous composite microstructures for solid oxide fuel cell anodes
